          <p>The central heating should keep the cottage cosy. To raise and lower the temperature temporarily use the arrow buttons on the thermostat, which is above the settee in front of the stairs.</p>
          <p>The log burner is laid ready should you want to use the fire as soon as you arrive and wood and kindling is provided in the baskets by the fire. If more is needed both wood and kindling can be found at local petrol stations, including the Esso garage in Haltwhistle.The fire is laid in the log burner and is ready to light as soon as you arrive with more wood and kindling provided in baskets by the hearth</p>
          <div class="mt-4 bg-yellow-50 p-4 rounded-lg">
            <h4 class="font-semibold mb-2">Important Safety Notes:</h4>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-4 space-y-2">
              <li>Keep the wood burner door closed for efficiency and safety</li>
              <li>Don't place wood or anything else on either side of the fire</li>
              <li>No need to clear out ash during your stay</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
